 Port Elizabeth - Four Ward by-elections are to be held on 18 September in four Eastern Cape municipalities. The IEC says these ward by-elections will be contested by 18 candidates. Nelson Mandela Bay Metro (Ward 20) Buffalo City Metro (Ward 19) Engcobo Local Municipality (Ward 15) King Sabata Dalindyebo Local Municipality (Ward 29) Thereafter, the next by election in the province will be held on 23 October 2019 due to the declaration of vacancies in the following municipalities: "The electoral commission is calling on residents in these wards to ensure they are registered and if not, to go and register in order to participate in the by elections that will be held on 23 October 2019.  Voting stations within the affected wards will be open for registration from 08h00 to 17h00 on both days, 07 & 08 September 2019," the IEC said. "A reminder that in order to be able to vote you need to be a registered voter and to bring your green bar-coded ID book, smart ID card or a valid temporary identity certificate with to the voting station." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 